pigeonpeas="""Pigeon pea (arhar)  resembles a pea in structure but has a pod that is flat in shape. It varies in size and color across different vegetation belts. Most commonly it is oval or white, brown, red, greyish or purplish in color with a white hylum. A rich source of protein, dietary fiber, thiamine, magnesium, phosphorous, potassium, copper and manganese, it also provides an adequate amount of iron and selenium."""
